Kansas City Royals and Chicago White Sox players involved in mass brawl during Thursday's game . 
  A heated exchange between Royals starter Yordano Ventura and White Sox outfielder Adam Eaton sparked the fight . 
  Umpires ejected a total of five players from both teams after the fight at Chicago's US Cellular Field in Illinois . 
  Several punches were thrown and Kansas City's Ventura, Lorenzo Cain and Edinson Volquez were ejected . 
  Chicago's Chris Sale and Jeff Samardzija also ejected . 
 